<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Bad-Variant-Access on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/bad-variant-access/</link><description>Recent content in Bad-Variant-Access on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/bad-variant-access/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] C++ std::bad_variant_access - alternative not valid</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/bad-variant-access/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/bad-variant-access/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="stdbad_variant_access---alternative-not-valid"&gt;std::bad_variant_access - alternative not valid&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;std::bad_variant_access&lt;/code&gt; is thrown when accessing a variant with the wrong type or index. This is the same exception as the wrong type variant.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: Index out of range
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;variant&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;float&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;double&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; v &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;42&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;auto&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; val &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;get&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;(v); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// throws — only 3 alternatives (0, 1, 2)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: Wrong type
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;variant&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;, std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;string&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; v &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;hello&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; i &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;get&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;(v); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// throws
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: Index-based access with wrong type
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;variant&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;, std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;string&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; v &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;hello&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; i &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;get&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;(v); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// throws — holds index 1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-check-index-with-index"&gt;Fix 1: Check index with index()&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (v.index() &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;==&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; val &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;get&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;(v);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-use-stdvisit"&gt;Fix 2: Use std::visit&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;visit([](&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;auto&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; val) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;cout &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; val &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;endl;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}, v);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-use-stdget_if"&gt;Fix 3: Use std::get_if&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;auto&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; p &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;get_if&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;v)) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;cout &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;p &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;endl;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/variant-bad-access/"&gt;std::bad_variant_access (wrong type)&lt;/a&gt; — type mismatch.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/bad-optional-access/"&gt;std::bad_optional_access&lt;/a&gt; — empty optional.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/any-cast-error/"&gt;std::bad_any_cast&lt;/a&gt; — any_cast failure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C++ std::bad_variant_access - wrong variant type</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/variant-bad-access/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/variant-bad-access/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="stdbad_variant_access---wrong-variant-type"&gt;std::bad_variant_access - wrong variant type&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;std::bad_variant_access&lt;/code&gt; is thrown when you call &lt;code&gt;std::get&amp;lt;T&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; on a &lt;code&gt;std::variant&lt;/code&gt; that does not currently hold type &lt;code&gt;T&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: Wrong type in get
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;variant&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;, std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;string&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; v &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;42&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;string s &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;get&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;string&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;(v); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// throws
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: Getting value without checking
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;variant&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;double&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; v &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3.14&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; i &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;get&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;(v); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// throws
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: Index out of range
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;variant&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;double&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; v &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;42&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; i &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;get&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;(v); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// throws — index 2 doesn&amp;#39;t exist
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-check-with-holds_alternative"&gt;Fix 1: Check with holds_alternative&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;holds_alternative&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;string&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;(v)) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;string s &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;get&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;string&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;(v);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-use-stdget_if-returns-nullptr"&gt;Fix 2: Use std::get_if (returns nullptr)&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;auto&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; p &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;get_if&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;string&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;v)) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;string s &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;p;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-use-stdvisit"&gt;Fix 3: Use std::visit&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;visit([](&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;auto&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; val) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;cout &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; val &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;endl;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}, v);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/bad-variant-access/"&gt;std::bad_variant_access (detailed)&lt;/a&gt; — detailed analysis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/bad-optional-access/"&gt;std::bad_optional_access&lt;/a&gt; — empty optional.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/any-cast-error/"&gt;std::bad_any_cast&lt;/a&gt; — any_cast failure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C++ std::bad_variant_access — Variant Type Mismatch Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/bad-variant-access-2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/bad-variant-access-2/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-stdbad_variant_access--variant-type-mismatch-fix"&gt;[Solution] C++ std::bad_variant_access — Variant Type Mismatch Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;std::bad_variant_access&lt;/code&gt; is thrown when &lt;code&gt;std::get&amp;lt;T&amp;gt;()&lt;/code&gt; is called on a &lt;code&gt;std::variant&lt;/code&gt; that does not currently hold a value of type &lt;code&gt;T&lt;/code&gt;. This commonly happens when code assumes a variant holds a specific type without checking first. The exception also occurs when accessing a variant that is valueless by exception.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="why-stdbad_variant_access-occurs"&gt;Why std::bad_variant_access Occurs&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common causes include calling &lt;code&gt;std::get&amp;lt;T&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; without first checking &lt;code&gt;std::holds_alternative&amp;lt;T&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt;, a variant becoming valueless after a throwing assignment, and using &lt;code&gt;std::get&lt;/code&gt; on a variant returned from a function that may hold any of its alternative types.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C++ std::variant Error — Variant Access Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/variant-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/variant-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-stdvariant-error--variant-access-fix"&gt;[Solution] C++ std::variant Error — Variant Access Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;std::variant&lt;/code&gt; error occurs when accessing a variant with the wrong type using &lt;code&gt;std::get&lt;/code&gt;, or when the variant is valueless by exception. &lt;code&gt;std::bad_variant_access&lt;/code&gt; is thrown on mismatched type access. Variants can also become valueless after a throwing assignment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="why-stdvariant-errors-occur"&gt;Why std::variant Errors Occur&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common causes include calling &lt;code&gt;std::get&amp;lt;T&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; without checking which type is active, variant becoming valueless after a throwing move constructor, using &lt;code&gt;std::get&lt;/code&gt; on a variant returned from an unknown source, and not handling all alternative types in visitation.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>